get.description:
Full RBAC registry snapshot for the audit matrix UI.

Response shape:
{
  "permissions": {
    "<name>": {"description": "...", "sensitive": bool}
  },
  "roles": {
    "<role>": ["<permission>", ...]
  },
  "routes": [
    {
      "method": "GET",
      "path": "/api/...",
      "permission": "plugins.read",
      "is_plugin_route": bool,
      "is_plugin_default": bool,
      "last_accessed": {
        "viewer": "<iso ts>" | null,
        "analyst": "<iso ts>" | null,
        ...
      }
    }
  ],
  "public_routes": [["GET", "/api/health"], ...],
  "audit_summary": {
    "window_hours": 24,
    "decisions": {"allow": N, "deny": M, "shadow_mismatch": K},
    "top_denials": [{"permission": "...", "count": N}, ...]
  },
  "shadow_mode": bool,
  "version": "0.9.8.3"
}

DeployKeyCreateResponse.description:
POST /api/settings/deploy-keys — returns the new key's identity + public material.

The private key is encrypted with NOUSVIZ_ENCRYPTION_KEY and stored;
the response intentionally omits it.
